<a name="content"></a>									
		<p class="lead"><strong>As you create your document, choices about the size of the margins and the
page orientation have a great effect on the appearance of it.</strong></p class="lead">

<p><strong>Margins</strong> are the blank space around the edges of the page. Good margins
improve the readability of a document. Some documents, like business letters,
are expected to have certain margin sizes, so knowing how to set the margins
for a document is important. The default setting is usually a margin of about
one inch on all four sides. Notice that you can set the margin for each side
separately.</p>

<p><strong>Page Orientation</strong> means to the direction of the document. The portrait
setting means vertical or longer side running top to bottom. The landscape
setting means horizontal or shorter side running top to bottom.</p>

<p>Settings for both margins and page orientation are found in the Page Setup
box. The Page Setup Box is the same for all versions, only accessing it differs.</p>


